# ğŸ¤– Model-Compose

**model-compose** is a declarative AI workflow orchestrator inspired by `docker-compose`. It lets you define and run AI model pipelines using simple YAML files â€” no custom code required. Effortlessly connect external AI services (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc.), run local AI models, integrate vector stores, and more â€” all within powerful, composable workflows.

**No custom code. Just YAML configuration.**

<div align="center">

[ğŸ“– User Guide](docs/user-guide/README.md) Â· [ğŸš€ Quick Start](#-quick-start) Â· [ğŸ’¡ Examples](examples/README.md) Â· [ğŸ¤ Contributing](#-contributing)

</div>

---

## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ¨ **No-Code AI Orchestration**
Define complex AI workflows entirely in YAMLâ€”no Python, no JavaScript, no coding required. Connect multiple AI services, models, and APIs through simple declarative configuration.

### ğŸ”— **Universal AI Service Integration**
Connect to any AI provider out of the boxâ€”OpenAI, Anthropic Claude, Google Gemini, ElevenLabs, Stability AI, Replicate, or any custom HTTP API. Mix and match services in a single workflow.

### ğŸ–¥ï¸ **Local Model Execution**
Run models from HuggingFace and other sources locally with native support for transformers, PyTorch, and model serving frameworks. Fine-tune models with LoRA/PEFT, train with custom datasets, all through YAML configuration.

### âš¡ **Real-Time Streaming**
Built-in SSE (Server-Sent Events) streaming for real-time AI responses. Stream from OpenAI, Claude, local models, or any streaming API with automatic chunking and connection management.

### ğŸ”„ **Advanced Workflow Composition**
Build multi-step pipelines with conditional logic, data transformation, and parallel execution. Pass data between jobs with powerful variable bindingâ€”`${input}`, `${response}`, `${env}`, with type conversion and defaults.

### ğŸš€ **Production-Ready Deployment**
Deploy as HTTP REST API or MCP (Model Context Protocol) server by changing one line. Includes concurrency control, health checks, and automatic API documentation.

### ğŸ¯ **Event-Driven Architecture**
HTTP Callback listeners for async workflows (image generation, video processing). HTTP Trigger listeners for webhooks and external events. Build reactive AI systems that respond to real-world events.

### ğŸŒ **Smart Tunneling & Gateways**
Expose local services to the internet instantly with ngrok, Cloudflare, or SSH tunnels. Perfect for webhook integration and public API deployment without complex networking.

### ğŸ³ **Container-Native Deployment**
First-class Docker support with runtime configuration, volume mounting, and environment management. Deploy to any cloud provider or Kubernetes cluster with minimal configuration.

### ğŸ¨ **Instant Web UI**
Add a visual interface with just 2 linesâ€”get Gradio-powered chat UI or serve custom static frontends. Test workflows, monitor executions, and debug pipelines visually.

### ğŸ—„ï¸ **RAG & Vector Database Ready**
Native integration with ChromaDB, Milvus, Pinecone, and Weaviate. Build retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems with embedding search, document indexing, and semantic retrieval.

### ğŸ”§ **Flexible Component System**
Reusable components with multi-action support. Define once, use everywhere. Mix HTTP clients, local models, vector stores, shell commands, and custom workflows in any combination.

