## ğŸ“¦ Installation

```
pip install model-compose
```

Or install from source:

```
git clone https://github.com/hanyeol/model-compose.git
cd model-compose
pip install -e .
```

> Requires: Python 3.9 or higher

---

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

Create a `model-compose.yml`:

```yaml
controller:
  type: http-server
  port: 8080
  webui:
    port: 8081

components:
  - id: chatgpt
    type: http-client
    base_url: https://api.openai.com/v1
    path: /chat/completions
    method: POST
    headers:
      Authorization: Bearer ${env.OPENAI_API_KEY}
    body:
      model: gpt-4o
      messages:
        - role: user
          content: ${input.prompt}

workflows:
  - id: chat
    default: true
    jobs:
      - component: chatgpt
```

Create a `.env` file:

```bash
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-key
```

Run it:

```bash
model-compose up
```

Your API is now live at `http://localhost:8080` and Web UI at `http://localhost:8081` ğŸ‰

---

## ğŸ¯ Powerful Yet Simple

### ğŸ–¥ï¸ Add Web UI with 2 Lines
```yaml
controller:
  webui:
    port: 8081
```

### ğŸ›°ï¸ Switch to MCP Server with 1 Line
```yaml
controller:
  type: mcp-server
```

### ğŸ”„ Run Components in Separate Processes
```yaml
component:
  runtime: process
```

### ğŸ³ Deploy in Docker with 1 Line
```yaml
controller:
  runtime: docker
```

> ğŸ’¡ Explore [examples](examples/README.md) for more workflows or read the [User Guide](docs/user-guide/README.md).

